# Tabby prose style

## Changelog tone

`CHANGELOG.md` is for **end users**. Keep each bullet to **one short line**. Say what Tabby does differently now, not how the code works.

### Length (Cursor AI)

- Aim for **one brief sentence**, often under 12 words.
- **Bold** one or two key words when it helps scanning.
- No parenthetical lists, no "and so on", no second clauses unless essential.

```markdown
# Good
- Separate words **speech** from the care menu, while still connected.
- Speech matches her **mood**.

# Bad
- When Tabby speaks up on her own, you see her words first. Tap her to open the care menu. Dismiss the bubble with ×, or close the care menu to clear both.
- When Tabby speaks up, her line matches how she feels (hungry, stressed, sleepy, and so on).
```

## No em dashes

Do **not** use em dashes (`—`) in:

- `CHANGELOG.md`, `README.md`, `PRIVACY.md`, store copy, UI strings
- `.cursor/rules/` and other project docs you write
- Comments meant for users or reviewers

Use instead:

- **Comma** or **period** for clause breaks
- **Colon** before a list or explanation
- **Hyphen-minus** (`-`) only for compound adjectives or bullet lists

```markdown
# Bad
Tabby reads only the title and URL — never page body text.

# Good
Tabby reads only the title and URL, never page body text.
```

This applies to new and edited text in the same task.
